Team Grey analysis from reviewing the data on the Top 10 Asian and Middle East Countries for Foreign Direct Investments. 
 China is stands out as the leader in overall value of the goods and services it produces to the USA economy and well as in the High Technology Exports just to name a few computers, aerospace, pharmaceuticals. Even though they may do the most, China makes its rather difficult amongst the global leaders to do business in their country. 
  Japan was the leader in investments made by Asian and Middle East Countries. Majority of their efforts going into manufacturing, managements or technology. They tripled the amount of investments then what the remaining top 10 leaders invested combined.
